<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="63" type="key">
<keyStep pageId="2" pageNumber="63">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1516,2007]" box="[151,1436,1516,1538]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,1516,1538]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">
1. Pronotum centrally with dense, granulate, and well-impressed microsculpture (
<figureCitation box="[984,1059,1516,1538]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1807,1831]" captionTargetBox="[265,1315,191,1773]" captionTargetId="figure-21@11.[261,1326,181,1783]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 2. Details of the external morphology in species of Pseudocanthon Bates, 1887. A, P. vazdemelloi new species pronotal disc; B, P. xanthurus (Blanchard, 1847) pronotal disc; C, P. vazdemelloi new species detail of left lateral of elytron; D, P. pantanensis new species detail of left lateral of elytron (arrow indicates eighth elytral stria present); E, P. perplexus (LeConte, 1847) protibia in dorsal view (arrow indicates median emargination); F, P. xanthurus (Blanchard, 1847) protibia in dorsal view; G. P. pantanensis new species pygidium; H, P. chaquensis new species pygidium. Scale bar: 0.5 mm (2A–D); 0.2 mm (2E–H)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5448092" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5448092/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
)............................. 2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1516,2007]" box="[151,1436,1545,1567]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,1545,1567]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,159,1545,1566]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">-</emphasis>
Pronotum centrally with inconspicuous microsculpture (
<figureCitation box="[766,839,1545,1567]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1807,1831]" captionTargetBox="[265,1315,191,1773]" captionTargetId="figure-21@11.[261,1326,181,1783]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 2. Details of the external morphology in species of Pseudocanthon Bates, 1887. A, P. vazdemelloi new species pronotal disc; B, P. xanthurus (Blanchard, 1847) pronotal disc; C, P. vazdemelloi new species detail of left lateral of elytron; D, P. pantanensis new species detail of left lateral of elytron (arrow indicates eighth elytral stria present); E, P. perplexus (LeConte, 1847) protibia in dorsal view (arrow indicates median emargination); F, P. xanthurus (Blanchard, 1847) protibia in dorsal view; G. P. pantanensis new species pygidium; H, P. chaquensis new species pygidium. Scale bar: 0.5 mm (2A–D); 0.2 mm (2E–H)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5448092" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5448092/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
)................................................ 4
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="2" pageNumber="63">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1516,2007]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="63">
2. Eighth elytral stria absent (
<figureCitation box="[482,555,1574,1596]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1807,1831]" captionTargetBox="[265,1315,191,1773]" captionTargetId="figure-21@11.[261,1326,181,1783]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 2. Details of the external morphology in species of Pseudocanthon Bates, 1887. A, P. vazdemelloi new species pronotal disc; B, P. xanthurus (Blanchard, 1847) pronotal disc; C, P. vazdemelloi new species detail of left lateral of elytron; D, P. pantanensis new species detail of left lateral of elytron (arrow indicates eighth elytral stria present); E, P. perplexus (LeConte, 1847) protibia in dorsal view (arrow indicates median emargination); F, P. xanthurus (Blanchard, 1847) protibia in dorsal view; G. P. pantanensis new species pygidium; H, P. chaquensis new species pygidium. Scale bar: 0.5 mm (2A–D); 0.2 mm (2E–H)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5448092" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5448092/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
) or reduced to basal one-fourth of elytra. Posterior edge of metafemora regularly curved, not projected towards the abdominal ventrites (
<figureCitation box="[642,718,1604,1626]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1868,1892]" captionTargetBox="[171,1413,608,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-218@13.[162,1424,597,1845]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 4. South American species of Pseudocanthon Bates, 1887, ventral view. A, Pseudocanthon perplexus (LeConte, 1847); B, P. xanthurus (Blanchard, 1847); C, P. vazdemelloi new species; D, P. pantanensis new species (arrows indicate angulation at posterior edge of metafemur); E, P. chaquensis new species (arrows indicate angulation at posterior edge of metafemur). Scale bar: 1 mm (3A–E); 2 mm (3F)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5448096" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5448096/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
). 
<collectingCountry box="[734,793,1604,1626]" name="Brazil" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[806,933,1604,1626]" country="Brazil" name="Mato Grosso" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Mato Grosso</collectingRegion>
) and 
<collectingCountry box="[985,1081,1604,1626]" name="Argentina" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Argentina</collectingCountry>
................................................................................... 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[888,1287,1632,1655]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">
<taxonomicName authority="Nazaré-Silva &amp; Silva, 2021" authorityName="Nazaré-Silva &amp; Silva" authorityYear="2021" box="[888,1163,1632,1654]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Pseudocanthon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vazdemelloi" status="new species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[888,1163,1632,1654]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Pseudocanthon vazdemelloi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1169,1287,1633,1655]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1300,1384,1633,1655]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1927,1951]" captionTargetBox="[292,1300,191,1893]" captionTargetId="figure-30@12.[280,1307,181,1903]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 3. South American species of Pseudocanthon Bates, 1887, dorsal view. A, Pseudocanthon perplexus (LeConte, 1847); B–C, P. xanthurus (Blanchard, 1847); D, P. vazdemelloi new species; E, P. pantanensis new species; F, P. chaquensis new species. Scale bar: 1 mm (3A–E); 2 mm (3F)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5448094" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5448094/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Figs. 3C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1394,1426,1633,1655]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1868,1892]" captionTargetBox="[171,1413,608,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-218@13.[162,1424,597,1845]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 4. South American species of Pseudocanthon Bates, 1887, ventral view. A, Pseudocanthon perplexus (LeConte, 1847); B, P. xanthurus (Blanchard, 1847); C, P. vazdemelloi new species; D, P. pantanensis new species (arrows indicate angulation at posterior edge of metafemur); E, P. chaquensis new species (arrows indicate angulation at posterior edge of metafemur). Scale bar: 1 mm (3A–E); 2 mm (3F)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5448096" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5448096/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">4C</figureCitation>
).
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1516,2007]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,159,1662,1683]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">-</emphasis>
Eighth elytral stria present and extending across approximately the basal half of elytra (
<figureCitation box="[1060,1137,1662,1684]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1807,1831]" captionTargetBox="[265,1315,191,1773]" captionTargetId="figure-21@11.[261,1326,181,1783]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 2. Details of the external morphology in species of Pseudocanthon Bates, 1887. A, P. vazdemelloi new species pronotal disc; B, P. xanthurus (Blanchard, 1847) pronotal disc; C, P. vazdemelloi new species detail of left lateral of elytron; D, P. pantanensis new species detail of left lateral of elytron (arrow indicates eighth elytral stria present); E, P. perplexus (LeConte, 1847) protibia in dorsal view (arrow indicates median emargination); F, P. xanthurus (Blanchard, 1847) protibia in dorsal view; G. P. pantanensis new species pygidium; H, P. chaquensis new species pygidium. Scale bar: 0.5 mm (2A–D); 0.2 mm (2E–H)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5448092" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5448092/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Fig. 2D</figureCitation>
). Posterior edge of metafemora slightly angulated at basal third, with expansion towards the abdominal ventrites (
<figureCitation box="[1012,1114,1692,1714]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1868,1892]" captionTargetBox="[171,1413,608,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-218@13.[162,1424,597,1845]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 4. South American species of Pseudocanthon Bates, 1887, ventral view. A, Pseudocanthon perplexus (LeConte, 1847); B, P. xanthurus (Blanchard, 1847); C, P. vazdemelloi new species; D, P. pantanensis new species (arrows indicate angulation at posterior edge of metafemur); E, P. chaquensis new species (arrows indicate angulation at posterior edge of metafemur). Scale bar: 1 mm (3A–E); 2 mm (3F)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5448096" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5448096/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Fig. 4D–E</figureCitation>
)......................... 3
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="2" pageNumber="63">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1516,2007]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="63">
<materialsCitation country="Brazil" location="Mato Grosso" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Mato Grosso">
3. Pygidium metallic green, with orange band at posterior edge (
<figureCitation box="[842,922,1721,1743]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1807,1831]" captionTargetBox="[265,1315,191,1773]" captionTargetId="figure-21@11.[261,1326,181,1783]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 2. Details of the external morphology in species of Pseudocanthon Bates, 1887. A, P. vazdemelloi new species pronotal disc; B, P. xanthurus (Blanchard, 1847) pronotal disc; C, P. vazdemelloi new species detail of left lateral of elytron; D, P. pantanensis new species detail of left lateral of elytron (arrow indicates eighth elytral stria present); E, P. perplexus (LeConte, 1847) protibia in dorsal view (arrow indicates median emargination); F, P. xanthurus (Blanchard, 1847) protibia in dorsal view; G. P. pantanensis new species pygidium; H, P. chaquensis new species pygidium. Scale bar: 0.5 mm (2A–D); 0.2 mm (2E–H)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5448092" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5448092/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Fig. 2G</figureCitation>
). Apex of parameres pointed in lateral view, curved towards the ventral edge of aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[594,669,1750,1772]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1919,1943]" captionTargetBox="[175,1410,894,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-346@16.[164,1422,885,1896]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 5. Aedeagus in South American species of Pseudocanthon Bates, 1887, lateral and ventral views, respectively. A, Pseudocanthon perplexus (LeConte, 1847); B–C, P. xanthurus (Blanchard, 1847) (arrows indicate variation at apex of parameres); D. P. vazdemelloi new species; E, P. pantanensis new species; F, P. chaquensis new species. Scale bar: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5448098" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5448098/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Fig. 5E</figureCitation>
). 
<collectingCountry box="[686,745,1750,1772]" name="Brazil" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[757,883,1750,1771]" country="Brazil" name="Mato Grosso" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Mato Grosso</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[930,1123,1750,1772]" country="Brazil" name="Mato Grosso do Sul" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Mato Grosso do Sul</collectingRegion>
).. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">
<taxonomicName authority="Nazaré-Silva &amp; Silva, 2021" authorityName="Nazaré-Silva &amp; Silva" authorityYear="2021" box="[1158,1437,1750,1772]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Pseudocanthon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pantanensis" status="new species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1158,1437,1750,1772]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Pseudocanthon pantanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[226,344,1779,1801]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[357,440,1780,1802]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1927,1951]" captionTargetBox="[292,1300,191,1893]" captionTargetId="figure-30@12.[280,1307,181,1903]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 3. South American species of Pseudocanthon Bates, 1887, dorsal view. A, Pseudocanthon perplexus (LeConte, 1847); B–C, P. xanthurus (Blanchard, 1847); D, P. vazdemelloi new species; E, P. pantanensis new species; F, P. chaquensis new species. Scale bar: 1 mm (3A–E); 2 mm (3F)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5448094" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5448094/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Figs. 3E</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[450,482,1780,1802]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1868,1892]" captionTargetBox="[171,1413,608,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-218@13.[162,1424,597,1845]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 4. South American species of Pseudocanthon Bates, 1887, ventral view. A, Pseudocanthon perplexus (LeConte, 1847); B, P. xanthurus (Blanchard, 1847); C, P. vazdemelloi new species; D, P. pantanensis new species (arrows indicate angulation at posterior edge of metafemur); E, P. chaquensis new species (arrows indicate angulation at posterior edge of metafemur). Scale bar: 1 mm (3A–E); 2 mm (3F)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5448096" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5448096/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">4D</figureCitation>
)
</materialsCitation>
.
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1516,2007]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,159,1809,1830]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">-</emphasis>
Pygidium completely orange (
<figureCitation box="[515,592,1809,1831]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1807,1831]" captionTargetBox="[265,1315,191,1773]" captionTargetId="figure-21@11.[261,1326,181,1783]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 2. Details of the external morphology in species of Pseudocanthon Bates, 1887. A, P. vazdemelloi new species pronotal disc; B, P. xanthurus (Blanchard, 1847) pronotal disc; C, P. vazdemelloi new species detail of left lateral of elytron; D, P. pantanensis new species detail of left lateral of elytron (arrow indicates eighth elytral stria present); E, P. perplexus (LeConte, 1847) protibia in dorsal view (arrow indicates median emargination); F, P. xanthurus (Blanchard, 1847) protibia in dorsal view; G. P. pantanensis new species pygidium; H, P. chaquensis new species pygidium. Scale bar: 0.5 mm (2A–D); 0.2 mm (2E–H)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5448092" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5448092/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Fig. 2H</figureCitation>
). Apex of parameres truncate, with small and obtuse projection at ventral edge (
<figureCitation box="[1353,1425,1809,1831]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1919,1943]" captionTargetBox="[175,1410,894,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-346@16.[164,1422,885,1896]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 5. Aedeagus in South American species of Pseudocanthon Bates, 1887, lateral and ventral views, respectively. A, Pseudocanthon perplexus (LeConte, 1847); B–C, P. xanthurus (Blanchard, 1847) (arrows indicate variation at apex of parameres); D. P. vazdemelloi new species; E, P. pantanensis new species; F, P. chaquensis new species. Scale bar: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5448098" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5448098/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Fig. 5F</figureCitation>
). 
<collectingCountry box="[226,283,1838,1860]" name="Brazil" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Brasil</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[296,423,1838,1860]" country="Brazil" name="Mato Grosso" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Mato Grosso</collectingRegion>
